  "chapter": {
    "number": 40,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Prepare the Way for the LORD"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Comfort, comfort My people,”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "says your God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Speak tenderly to Jerusalem,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and proclaim to her",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "that her forced labor has been completed;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "her iniquity has been pardoned.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For she has received from the hand of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "double for all her sins.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "A voice of one calling:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Prepare the way for the LORD in the wilderness;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2644
          },
          {
            "text": "make a straight highway for our God in the desert.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2645
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Every valley shall be lifted up,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and every mountain and hill made low;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the uneven ground will become smooth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the rugged land a plain.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2646
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And the glory of the LORD will be revealed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and all humanity together will see it.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2647
          },
          "For the mouth of the LORD has spoken.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Enduring Word"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A voice says, “Cry out!”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "And I asked, “What should I cry out?”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“All flesh is like grass,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and all its glory like the flowers of the field.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The grass withers and the flowers fall",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when the breath of the LORD blows on them;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "indeed, the people are grass.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The grass withers and the flowers fall,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the word of our God stands forever.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2648
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Here Is Your God!"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Go up on a high mountain,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O Zion, herald of good news.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Raise your voice loudly,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O Jerusalem, herald of good news.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Lift it up,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2649
          },
          {
            "text": "do not be afraid!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Say to the cities of Judah,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Here is your God!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, the Lord GOD comes with might,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and His arm establishes His rule.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "His reward is with Him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and His recompense accompanies Him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He tends His flock like a shepherd;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He gathers the lambs in His arms",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and carries them close to His heart.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He gently leads the nursing ewes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who has measured the waters in the hollow of his hand,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or marked off the heavens with the span of his hand?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Who has held the dust of the earth in a basket,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or weighed the mountains on a scale",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the hills with a balance?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who has directed the Spirit of the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2650
          },
          {
            "text": "or informed Him as His counselor?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2651
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whom did He consult to enlighten Him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and who taught Him the paths of justice?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Who imparted knowledge to Him",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and showed Him the way of understanding?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely the nations are like a drop in a bucket;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they are considered a speck of dust on the scales;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He lifts up the islands",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2652
          },
          {
            "text": "like fine dust.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Lebanon is not sufficient for fuel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor its animals enough for a burnt offering.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All the nations are as nothing before Him;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He regards them as nothingness and emptiness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "To whom will you liken God?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "To what image will you compare Him?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "To an idol that a craftsman casts",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a metalworker overlays with gold",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and fits with silver chains?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "To one bereft of an offering",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who chooses wood that will not rot,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who seeks a skilled craftsman",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to set up an idol that will not topple?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do you not know?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Have you not heard?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Has it not been declared to you from the beginning?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Have you not understood since the foundation of the earth?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He sits enthroned above the circle of the earth;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "its dwellers are like grasshoppers.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He stretches out the heavens like a curtain,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and spreads them out like a tent to dwell in.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He brings the princes to nothing",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and makes the rulers",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2653
          },
          {
            "text": "of the earth meaningless.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "No sooner are they planted, no sooner are they sown,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no sooner have their stems taken root in the ground,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "than He blows on them and they wither,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a whirlwind sweeps them away like stubble.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“To whom will you liken Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or who is My equal?” asks the Holy One.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Lift up your eyes on high:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Who created all these?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He leads forth the starry host by number;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He calls each one by name.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Because of His great power and mighty strength,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "not one of them is missing.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why do you say, O Jacob,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and why do you assert, O Israel,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“My way is hidden from the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my claim is ignored by my God”?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do you not know?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Have you not heard?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The LORD is the everlasting God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Creator of the ends of the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He will not grow tired or weary;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "His understanding is beyond searching out.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He gives power to the faint",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and increases the strength of the weak.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Even youths grow tired and weary,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and young men stumble and fall.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But those who wait upon the LORD will renew their strength;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will mount up with wings like eagles;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they will run and not grow weary,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will walk and not faint.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
